description: Used by the compiler for classes with [RoyaleArrayLike] metadata when processing for-in/for-each-in loops

values: forInstance the instance to be checked
lengthCheck either a string that represents a property to return length value, or a function method reference, e.g. instance.length()
getAt the String name of the accessor for the item at index... e.g. 'getItemAt'. If null it will default to Array Access []
lengthIsMethodCall true if the length accessor is an explicit method call instead of a getter
keys true if the request is to iterate over keys (as opposed to values)
a lightweight iterator Object with hasNext() and next() methods
